{"TopicId":191542,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Control group function to toggle fuel tanks.","CreatedByName":"boolybooly","CreatedById":6572,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-10T23:42:17Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"boolybooly","CreatedById":6572,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-10T23:42:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cs\u003Esince fuel prioritisation has been taken away and\u003C/s\u003E aerodynamics remain a challenge, with some designs\u00A0requiring careful management of the center of mass and therefore fuel drain, it would help if one could lock or unlock a fuel tank with a hotkey using a custom control group function to toggle flow from the tank instead of having to micro the little green arrows in the right click popup\u00A0\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-02-13T20:14:15Z\u0022 title=\u002202/13/2020 08:14  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 13, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by boolybooly\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-11T06:27:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223739059\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191542\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221581378137\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00226572\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022boolybooly\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, boolybooly said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsince fuel prioritisation has been taken away\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow do you mean? Tank priority is an advanced tweakable, unless you mean something other than that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"swjr-swis","CreatedById":152460,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-11T16:11:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223739059\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191542\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221581378137\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00226572\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022boolybooly\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 hours ago, boolybooly said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit would help if one could lock or unlock a fuel tank with a hotkey using a custom control group function to toggle flow from the tan\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI fully agree with this part. Would love to add fuel lock as a toggle to action groups, for all kinds of practical (and some non-practical) reasons.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223739059\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191542\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221581378137\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00226572\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022boolybooly\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 hours ago, boolybooly said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsince fuel prioritisation has been taken away\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou may have started a new game and forgot that \u0027Advanced Tweakables\u0027 are a thing? Looks for it in the settings. Flow priority can still be set, even on the fly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223739059\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191542\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221581378137\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00226572\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022boolybooly\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 hours ago, boolybooly said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\naerodynamics remain a challenge\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would disagree. It has its own rules and quirks, but there\u0027s also a lot of freedom to make things fly that have no business being in the air. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223739059\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191542\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221581378137\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u00226572\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022boolybooly\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 hours ago, boolybooly said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwith some designs\u00A0requiring careful management of the center of mass and therefore fuel drain\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s all about checking wet and dry \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E positions while building. Adding a single small tank on a strategic place can often be enough to balance things out. Sometimes, all it needs is to simply not fill all tanks completely. One trick can be to build with emptied tanks, and only start fueling up when you have the design mostly ready.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"boolybooly","CreatedById":6572,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-02-13T19:49:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223739155\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022191542\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221581402459\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/11/2020 at 6:27 AM, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow do you mean? Tank priority is an advanced tweakable, unless you mean something other than that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAh! \u00A0My mistake. I\u00A0haven\u0027t used tank priority for a while and forgot it was an advanced tweakable. Thanks \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIts a global setting applying to all gamesaves but\u00A0I think it must have reverted to default off\u00A0when\u00A0I\u00A0reinstalled.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyway the toggling tank\u00A0flow by control key suggestion still stands.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}